line_2: Fair Sylvia stood foremost in right of her claim,

line_1: When to crown the high transports dear conquest excites,
line_2: At court she was envy'd and toasted at White's.

line_1: At court she was envy'd and toasted at White's.
line_2: When to crown the high transports dear conquest excites,

line_1: But how shall I whisper this fair one's sad case?
line_2: A cruel disease has spoil'd her sweet face;

line_1: A cruel disease has spoil'd her sweet face;
line_2: But how shall I whisper this fair one's sad case?

line_1: Her vermillion is chang'd to a dull settled red,
line_2: And all the gay graces of beauty are fled.

line_1: And all the gay graces of beauty are fled.
line_2: Her vermillion is chang'd to a dull settled red,

line_1: Yet take heed, all ye fair, how you triumph in vain,
line_2: For Sylvia, tho' alter'd from pretty to plain,

line_1: For Sylvia, tho' alter'd from pretty to plain,
line_2: Yet take heed, all ye fair, how you triumph in vain,

line_1: Is now more engaging fince reason took place,
line_2: Than when she possess'd the perfections of face.

line_1: Than when she possess'd the perfections of face.
line_2: Is now more engaging fince reason took place,

line_1: Convinc'd she no more can coquet it and teaze,
line_2: Instead of tormenting — she studies to please:

line_1: Instead of tormenting — she studies to please:
line_2: Convinc'd she no more can coquet it and teaze,

line_1: Makes truth and discretion the guide of her life,
line_2: And tho' spoil'd for a toast, she's well form'd for a wife.
